It #8217;s called a Chochlear implant and they basically replicate the little hairs in your chochlea with tiny chips, but it will not restore your hearing to be even close to what the natural cochlea is able to pick up. It #8217;s actually pretty controversial among the deaf community to have your child get the surgery done since there is the alternative of accepting the kid is deaf and teaching them sign language while learning it yourself. Some people see it as offensive since they believe being deaf should not be considered a disability and frankly I #8217;m not sure what I truly believe as a hearing person. I don #8217;t know if this should be seen as selfish or not, but I know one thing for sure. This kid and his parents should still learn sign language, because he is still very very hard of hearing and it will be much harder for him if his parents try to exclude him from the deaf community.
